replies.body:
Yeah... They've said the more fragments you get the less likely they are to drop, and that the drop rate will reset every month. I got 6 chests and could only open 2 via key drops, I ended up buying the keys with RP because I was getting impatient. 

On a tangent, I think the chests should drop a small amount of essence with each shard, I've got two skin shards that I can't even activate because I don't have enough essence and I've already disenchanted a couple of shards too.
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}

Neither have I, I currently have 2 chest sitting in my inventory waiting to be opened but I haven't had a single key fragment in ages since release. 


{{item:3070}}{{item:3151}} 

{{sticker:zombie-nunu-tears}} 


In my honest opinion, I would say that the key fragment system doesn't really need to exist when we are already gated by the limited number of chests which is 1 a week or 4 a month which is only obtained by getting an S rank or by being in a party with someone who got an S on a champion whom you have not previously obtained a chest from.  If you ask me the non-linear key fragment drop system just adds to frustration and isn't really intuitive. 

So on 4 champions a month we may earn a chest each from the pool of 130 champions. 

It'll take several years to unlock a chest for each champion.

My bad then, but that only proves my point even more.

I thought the chest slot was to regenerate a week from its use, not 1 per week ;~;

Eh, I'll correct it now
